VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Medicare, Social Security, there\'s all kinds of things that the government does run. Um, but we don\'t want to be overly reliant on the government. We don\'t want to put all of our eggs in one basket. So, these models are proven, legally sturdy, and scalable from a single firm'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to an entire county. Uh, some of them are scalable up to the state and federal level as well. Um, through extensive research, I found uh a ton of options, and I\'ve actually got a blog post that has many more options over on Substack.'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Um, so ESOPS and patron equity, employee and customer share programs let workers buy uh workers or buyers earn equity uh slices that pay out as firms grow. So ESOPs are pretty well established. And'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then patron equity is one of the slightly novel innovations where it\'s like an ESOP, but instead of instead of earning shares from working there, you actually earn shares by shopping there. Uh so it\'s the same principle but it\'s'

[01:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just you expand it so that uh for instance if you have a local company that you shop at you earn more equity the more you shop there so that you become uh an owner of the establishment. Um which then means that as the economy'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'grows as that company grows uh so does your wealth. Um so that\'s something that you have direct control over and the government doesn\'t need to participate at all. Now some people have said well Dave wouldn\'t companies do this already?'

